Think your skincare routine ends with creams and sunscreen? Think again.

If you’re still getting rashes, breakouts, or irritation, your fabric might be to blame. Heavy or synthetic materials trap heat and don’t let your skin breathe, especially in this humidity.

The fix? LIVA fabric – made from plant-based fibres that feel light, soft, and oh-so-gentle on your skin. It keeps you cool, comfy, and irritation-free, all while being kind to the planet. 

Just look for the pink LIVA tag when you shop. Because skincare isn’t only about what goes on your skin—it’s also about what touches it all day.
Check: www.livabybirlacellulose.com to know how you can find a LIVA pink tag garment. 

#WearBetter #SkinFriendlyFabric #LIVASOS #EcoStyle #SmartSkincare #LIVAFabrics #LIVAEarthCare #SwitchToLiva

Nature doesn’t follow trends,  it creates them.​

With Spunshades, these hues don’t just sit on the fabric. They’re part of the fibre,  locked in through a dope-dye process that’s kinder to the planet and designed to last.⁠​

⁠No fading. No dyeing. No water wasted. Just colour that feels as natural as the landscapes it came from.​

Did you know your skin health is directly linked to the fabric used to create your outfit?

Wearing the wrong material can cause irritation, acne, rashes—even infections. But there’s a smarter, skin-friendly alternative: LIVA fabric. 🌿

Crafted from plant-based fibres, LIVA is breathable, ultra-soft, and gentle on your skin—perfect for all-day comfort in any season. Bonus? It’s eco-conscious and sustainably made, so your style choices stay kind to the planet too.

Next time you shop, look for the LIVA pink tag on the garments—because your skin (and the earth) deserve the very best.
